comments.body:
@Luap99 if you intend to also bump the memory size of the VMs in this PR, one word of caution:

GCP is "funny" about the CPUs-to-Memory ratio.  It's weirdly complex, like the # CPUs must be <= 1/2 Ram Gb.  In any case, you'll get a mostly-readable error message if it's not happy with the values.

Also in case it helps, you can now specify the [GCP VM's by `type:` name](https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/general-purpose-machines) (similar to how AWS does it).  This may be a better way to go (now or in the future) because not all "types" are created equal: Some use newer/better/faster CPU models, or come with built-in optomizations.  IIRC, if you specify CPU/RAM instead of `type:`, it gives you "first available" which may not be the latest/greatest Intel/AMD CPU.
